    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good start, helps us narrow the scope. When you say their background is 'almost certainly' rooted in those European or old-American wealth structures, do you mean that we should focus our marketing almost exclusively on those specific racial or ethnic groups to get the best ROI? Like, are there other demographics we should even bother looking at for this tier of product, or is the luxury market pretty much limited to those traditional profiles?",
